      <div style="font-size:13px;color:#64748b;margin-bottom:12px;">Pay minimums on everything, throw any extra at the highest-interest debt first.</div>
      <ol style="font-size:13px;color:#1e293b;padding-left:20px;line-height:2;">
        <li><strong style="color:#ef4444;">Apple Card</strong> — highest interest rate, balance growing</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#eab308;">Discover</strong> — likely high rate, small balance = quick win</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#3b82f6;">EECU LOC</strong> — small balance, LOC rate</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#64748b;">Auto Loan</strong> — lowest rate, keep at minimum</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:16px;padding:12px;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.2);border-radius:8px;">
      <div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#22c55e;margin-bottom:4px;">Quick win: Discover + LOC</div>
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:#64748b;">Both can be eliminated within 14 months at current minimums. Frees up $158/mo that can attack the Apple Card balance.</div>
